Skoda Vagonka to Make Locomotives With Ukraine, Kommersant Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-04-18T07:10:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/skoda-vagonka-to-make-locomotives-with-ukraine-kommersant-says.html
Ukrainian state rail operator
Ukrzaliznytsya is in talks with Skoda Vagonka AS, a Czech
rolling stock and locomotive manufacturer, to jointly produce
electric locomotives,  Kommersant-Ukraine  newspaper reported,
citing Mykola Serhienko, first deputy chief executive officer of
Ukrzaliznytsya.  The companies, which are discussing signing a joint venture
memorandum in May, will produce 20 locomotives, five in the
 Czech Republic  and 15 in Ukraine, according to Kommersant.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 